@misc{freelancermapGmb2025,
   abstract = {The Freelancer Study is the result of an international
survey among freelancers and independent professio-
nals. For the ninth time, the study analyzes working con-
ditions, pricing and income trends, acquisition strategies,
satisfaction levels, and both professional and structural
challenges in the freelancing industry.

A total of 3,571 freelancers and self-employed
professionals were surveyed between January 13, 2025,
and March 9, 2025. The results are further enriched by
insights from freelancers, companies, and 16 industry
and subject matter experts.

